Zainab Chidzuga died on Thursday, August 12, 2021. [File, Standard]  Former Kwale Woman Representative Zainab Chidzuga is dead.  Chidzuga died on Thursday, August 12 while undergoing treatment at the Nairobi Hospital, her son Hassan Chidzuga told The Standard.  It wasn’t immediately clear what the former lawmaker was ailing from. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. President Uhuru Kenyatta eulogised Chidzuga as a women’s rights champion.  Chidzuga faces opposition in race for Kwale Woman Rep seat  Legislator dismisses Mung'aro ouster  MP's aide wanted on defilement charges  CORD MPs fault Government over truth report “She was a passionate advocate of women empowerment whose many achievements as an activist, legislator and mentor will continue shaping the gender agenda in our country for generations,” said the President.  Deputy President William Ruto described Chidzuga as a “selfless and visionary leader who served the people of Kwale with dedication,” adding: “She was progressive, steadfast and focused”.  Chidzuga served as Kwale Woman Representative between 2013 and 2017. She was sponsored to the seat on ODM ticket.   A section of CORD elected leaders in Coast province claim they are tired of being in the oppositio  Supremacy battle pitting Zainab Chidzuga and governor Salim Mvurya plays out in public  ODM leaders in coast exchange bitter words in front of party leader Raila Odinga over party loyalty By Betty Njeru | 2 hours ago By Betty Njeru | 2 hours ago By Roselyne Obala | 5 hours ago By Ndungu Gachane | 5 hours ago